      "description": "5 hours after the second Thymidine-block release, cells were imaged at 37°C every 20 minutes for 18 hours (for a total tracking of 23 hours). For each field of view, 3 z-sections spaced at 6 µm each were taken. Fluorescence detected in the 488 nm channel was used to assess transgene expression (mNeonGreen PLK1 or Bora), while the 647 nm channel was employed to visualize cells DNA via SiRDNA staining. A brightfield image was acquired in parallel . ",
